## Summary

This room covers the fundamentals of shells used in penetration testing — reverse shells, bind shells, shell listeners, and shell payloads across multiple languages. The practical task required exploiting two real vulnerabilities: a command injection vulnerability using a reverse shell, and an unrestricted file upload vulnerability using a PHP web shell. Both flags were retrieved from the `/` directory of the target server.

## Tools Used

- `nc` (netcat) — shell listener
- `bash` — reverse shell payload
- `PHP` — web shell payload
- `nmap` — port scanning
- Browser — web application interaction

