## Key Concepts

### Reverse Shell vs Bind Shell

| Type | How it works | When to use |
|------|-------------|-------------|
| **Reverse Shell** | Target connects back to attacker | When target is behind firewall |
| **Bind Shell** | Attacker connects to target | When attacker is behind firewall |

### Shell Payloads by Language

| Language | Priority | Use case |
|----------|----------|---------|
| Bash | ⭐⭐⭐ Must know | Most Linux targets |
| Python | ⭐⭐⭐ Must know | When bash fails |
| PHP | ⭐⭐ Important | Web app attacks |
| BusyBox | ⭐ Good to know | Embedded/IoT devices |

### File Descriptors

| Number | What it is |
|--------|-----------|
| `0` | stdin (input) |
| `1` | stdout (output) |
| `2` | stderr (errors) |
| `3`+ | custom file descriptors |

